    • Method Detail

      • mergeParcelable

        @NotNull
public static <OUT> ChannelsBuilder<? extends Channel<?,ParcelableSelectable<OUT>>> mergeParcelable(@NotNull
                                                                                                             Channel<?,?>... channels)
        Returns a builder of channels merging the specified channels into a selectable one.
        The selectable indexes will be the position in the array.

        Note that the builder will successfully create only one channel instance, and that the passed ones will be bound as a result of the creation.
        Note also that the returned channel will be already closed.

        Type Parameters:
        OUT - the output data type.
        Parameters:
        channels - the channels to merge.
        Returns:
        the selectable channel builder.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified array is empty.
        NullPointerException - if the specified array is null or contains a null object.
        See Also:
        Channels.merge(Channel...)

      • parcelableByteChannel

        @NotNull
public static ParcelableByteChannel parcelableByteChannel(int dataBufferSize)
        Returns a new byte channel.
        Since the byte buffers generated by the channel are likely to be part of a remote procedure call, be aware of the limits imposed by the Android OS architecture when choosing a specific buffer size (see TransactionTooLargeException).
        Parameters:
        dataBufferSize - the size of the data buffer used to transfer the bytes through the routine channels.
        Returns:
        the byte channel.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified size is 0 or negative.

      • parcelableByteChannel

        @NotNull
public static ParcelableByteChannel parcelableByteChannel(int dataBufferSize,
                                                                   int corePoolSize)
        Returns a new byte channel.
        Since the byte buffers generated by the channel are likely to be part of a remote procedure call, be aware of the limits imposed by the Android OS architecture when choosing a specific buffer size (see TransactionTooLargeException).
        Parameters:
        dataBufferSize - the size of the data buffer used to transfer the bytes through the routine channels.
        corePoolSize - the maximum number of data retained in the pool. Additional data created to fulfill the bytes requirement will be discarded.
        Returns:
        the byte channel.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified size is 0 or negative.

      • selectableOutputParcelable

        @NotNull
public static <OUT> ChannelsBuilder<? extends Channel<?,ParcelableSelectable<OUT>>> selectableOutputParcelable(@NotNull
                                                                                                                        Channel<?,? extends OUT> channel,
                                                                                                                        int index)
        Returns a builder of channels making the specified one selectable.
        Each output will be passed along unchanged.

        Note that the builder will successfully create only one channel instance, and that the passed one will be bound as a result of the creation.
        Note also that the returned channel will be already closed.

        Type Parameters:
        OUT - the output data type.
        Parameters:
        channel - the channel to make selectable.
        index - the channel index.
        Returns:
        the selectable channel builder.
        See Also:
        Channels.selectableOutput(Channel, int)
